ly transaction feeds to autonomous supervisor workers that execute continuous matching DAGs, auditing records in memory and alerting system deviations without storing sensitive banking PII.\";\n310 |       roiEstimate = \"Reduces ledger reconciliation validation times by 84% and flags ledger drift under 150ms.\";\n311 |       squad = [\n312 |         { name: \"AS-09 Balance Auditor\", subtitle: \"Ledger Reconciliation Node\", description: \"Performs continuous double-entry ledger sweeps and maps account discrepancies across legacy databases.\", code: \"ACTIVE_SWEEPER_NODE\" },\n313 |         { name: \"PL-02 Compliance Sentry\", subtitle: \"Regulated Telemetry Guardian\", description: \"Ensures compliance with standard auditing protocols, scrubbing transaction records before in-memory execution.\", code: \"SOC2_MEM_SHIELD\" },\n314 |         { name: \"SV-04 Consensus Orchestrator\", subtitle: \"Multi-Agent DAG Coordinator\", description: \"Coordinates operational validation handoffs, compiling verified state logs into encrypted database tables.\", code: \"SUPERVISOR_CORE\" }\n315 |       ];\n316 |     } else if (data.ind === \"Healthcare\") {\n317 |       proposal = \"Deploy a local HIPAA-Compliant Medical Note Parsing and Clinical Vector Mesh. Designed with absolute zero-retention memory locks, this system maps unstructured clinical records and medical charts to secure local vector stores, allowing diagnostic staff to query internal documents safely without cloud-transit leakage.\";\n318 |       roiEstimate = \"Saves medical analysts an average of 14 hours per week on document transcription and retrieval.\";\n319 |       squad = [\n320 |         { name: \"MD-05 Privacy Watchdog\", subtitle: \"PII Sanitizer & Log Anchor\", description: \"Scrubs sensitive clinical identifiers from ingestion memory buffers, locking data access profiles to on-prem VPCs.\", code: \"ZERO_KNOWLEDGE_PII\" },\n321 |         { name: \"NX-14 Clinical Synthesizer\", subtitle: \"Document Mapping Expert\", description: \"Parses complex handwritten and typed records, translating medical documentation into structured vector graphs.\", code: \"CLINICAL_GRAPH_MESH\" },\n322 |         { name: \"SV-12 Healthcare Supervisor\", subtitle: \"Medical SLA Evaluator\", description: \"Enforces diagnostic accuracy logs and verifies clinical taxonomy classifications before indexing database rows.\", code: \"ACCURACY_MONITOR\" }\n323 |       ];\n324 |     } else if (data.ind === \"Retail\") {\n325 |       proposal = \"Architect a Sovereign Freight Ledger & Logistics Auditing Pipeline. This optimization system analyzes carrier dispatch invoices, maps overland shipping manifests against GPS trackers, and detects inventory route delays. It automatically reports invoice anomalies and calculates shipping penalty credits.\";\n326 |       roiEstimate = \"Reclaims an estimated 4.2% of logistics expenditure by flagging duplicate billing and routing errors.\";\n327 |       squad = [\n328 |         { name: \"LG-03 Logistics Evaluator\", subtitle: \"Freight Manifest Parser\", description: \"Extracts container carrier specs and audits freight manifests across fragmented invoice formats.\", code: \"LOGISTICS_DAG\" },\n329 |         { name: \"RT-11 Route Optimization Node\", subtitle: \"Geospatial Delay Assessor\", description: \"Ingests route history and mapping metrics, flagging bottlenecks in active land-freight lanes.\", code: \"GEOSPATIAL_ANALYZER\" },\n330 |         { name: \"SV-05 Contract Guard\", subtitle: \"SLA Penalty Trigger\", description: \"Tracks carrier delivery contracts and compiles automated late-delivery reimbursement requests.\", code: \"SLA_ENFORCER\" }\n331 |       ];\n332 |     } else if (isSearching) {\n333 |       proposal = `Deploy a local Semantic Knowledge Graph and Document Retrieval Mesh tailored for ${industryName}. The system implements private embedding models to index corporate documents, technical files, and siloed internal files, responding to employees with accurate, cited answers while enforcing strict role-based data access.`;\n334 |       roiEstimate = \"Reduces time wasted searching for cross-department files by 78%, boosting operational agility.\";\n335 |       squad = [\n336 |         { name: \"KG-07 Graph Synthesizer\", subtitle: \"Semantic Mapping Node\", description: \"Constructs semantic nodes from siloed documentation, mapping internal database connections.\", code: \"SEMANTIC_INDEXER\" },\n337 |         { name: \"SV-04 Access Boundary Node\", subtitle: \"Security Credentials Watchdog\", description: \"Validates active corporate user access and filters query responses based on document clearance levels.\", code: \"IAM_GUARDRAIL\" },\n338 |         { name: \"AS-15 Semantic Retriever\", subtitle: \"Low-Latency Search Executor\", description: \"Executes in-memory semantic queries across enterprise documents, delivering synthesized, cited summaries.\", code: \"RETRIEVAL_SWARM\" }\n339 |       ];\n340 |     } else if (isManual) {\n341 |       proposal = `Establish an Automated Multi-Agent Process Engine for ${industryName} workflows. This system deploys cooperative agents that replace manual file routing, cross-system copy-pasting, and repetitive review handoffs, recording all actions to an encrypted audit timeline.`;\n342 |       roiEstimate = \"Cuts department process cycle-times by 62% and maintains absolute compliance tracking logs.\";\n343 |       squad = [\n344 |         { name: \"WF-12 Queue Master\", subtitle: \"Task Routing Agent\", description: \"Senses newly received files, checks payload integrity, and delegates assignments across specialized agents.\", code: \"QUEUE_ROUTER\" },\n345 |         { name: \"AS-08 Data Sync Agent\", subtitle: \"Multi-Platform Database Updater\", description: \"Safely reads and writes verified values across legacy ERPs and modern database clusters.\", code: \"LEGACY_CONNECTOR\" },\n346 |         { name: \"SV-02 Policy Guardian\", subtitle: \"Execution Authenticator\", description: \"Ensures every automated action matches organizational guidelines, raising flags on anomalous requests.\", code: \"POLICY_ENFORCER\" }\n347 |       ];\n348 |     } else {\n349 |       proposal = `Configure a custom Sovereign Cognitive Swarm optimized for: \"${data.desc.slice(0, 75)}...\". The setup embeds dedicated agent pipelines inside a private environment, ensuring automated processing, safety checks, and strict data boundaries.`;\n350 |       roiEstimate = \"Boosts execution throughput by 55% while maintaining single-tenant data isolation.\";\n351 |       squad = [\n352 |         { name: \"AS-01 Core Executor\", subtitle: \"Task Processing Worker\", description: \"Executes primary analytical steps and organizes processed database files.\", code: \"CORE_WORKER\" },\n353 |         { name: \"SV-08 Security Supervisor\", subtitle: \"Enclave Boundary Guardian\", description: \"Enforces air-gapped container boundaries, logging active agent statuses.\", code: \"ENCLAVE_SHIELD\" },\n354 |         { name: \"AN-10 Telemetry Collector\", subtitle: \"Performance & ROI Tracker\", description: \"Records token latency and operational savings metric points, rendering local telemetry reports.\", code: \"ANALYTICS_NODE\" }\n355 |       ];\n356 |     }\n357 | \n358 |     const phase1Duration = data.urgency === \"Urgent\" ? \"7 Days\" : \"14 Days\";\n359 |     const phase2Duration = data.urgency === \"Urgent\" ? \"21 Days\" : \"30 Days\";\n360 |     const phase3Duration = data.urgency === \"Urgent\" ? \"30 Days\" : \"45 Days\";\n361 | \n362 |     const aiIntegrationFocus = data.aiStage === \"Production\" \n363 |       ? \"Integrate with active model mesh and existing vector stores.\"\n364 |       : \"Establish core private LLM instances and local embedding pipelines.\";\n365 | \n366 |     timeline = [\n367 |       {\n368 |         phase: \"Phase 1: GARAGE Co-Innovation\",\n369 |         duration: phase1Duration,\n370 |         details: `Map existing legacy connectors and document schemas. Setup a zero-trust local prototype workspace in an isolated sandbox. Define API boundaries and secure data ingestion criteria.`,\n371 |         target: \"Sovereign Proof-of-Concept blueprint and architectural clearance sign-off.\"\n372 |       },\n373 |       {\n374 |         phase: \"Phase 2: FOUNDRY Core Assembly\",\n375 |         duration: phase2Duration,\n376 |         details: `Deploy and calibrate your customized multi-agent squad. ${aiIntegrationFocus} Build secure workflow DAGs and wrap the deployment into dedicated single-tenant VPC containers.`,\n377 |         target: \"Air-gapped pre-production environment with verified security guardrails.\"\n378 |       },\n379 |       {\n380 |         phase: \"Phase 3: FACTORY Scale & Monitor\",\n381 |         duration: phase3Duration,\n382 |         details: `Transition workflows into live operations. Activate supervisor nodes for continuous runtime compliance auditing, token telemetry, error-handling validation, and ROI monitoring.`,\n383 |         target: \"Full production-grade launch with 24/7 sovereign telemetry logging and SLA compliance.\"\n384 |       }\n385 |     ];\n386 | \n387 |     return { proposal, squad, timeline, roiEstimate };\n388 |   };\n389 | \n390 |   const results = showResults ? compileDeterministicResults() : null;\n391 | \n392 |   return (\n393 |     <ToolPageShell showContact={false}>\n394 |       {/* Title section */}\n395 |       <div className=\"border-b border-white/5 pb-8 mb-10 flex flex-col lg:flex-row lg:items-end justify-between gap-6\">\n396 |         <div className=\"space-y-3 max-w-4xl\">\n397 |           <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-[#009DFF] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest block\">\n398 |             INTAKE & ARCHITECTURE SIMULATOR\n399 |           </span>\n400 |           <h1 className=\"text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white tracking-tight leading-none\">\n401 |             AI Challenge <span className=\"text-[#009DFF]\">Intake Console</span>\n402 |           </h1>\n403 |           <p className=\"text-white/50 text-xs lg:text-sm font-light leading-relaxed max-w-2xl\">\n404 |             Submit your enterprise operational friction to compile optimized multi-agent squad layouts, strategic proposed directions, and a deterministic 90-day sandbox deployment timeline.\n405 |           </p>\n406 |         </div>\n407 |         <div className=\"p-4 px-6 rounded-xl bg-white/[0.01] border border-white/5 flex flex-col items-start min-w-[220px] shrink-0\">\n408 |           <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase tracking-widest\">SECURE PORTAL STATUS</span>\n409 |           <span className=\"text-sm font-bold text-[#00FF9D] mt-1 font-mono tracking-tight flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n410 |             <span className=\"w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#00FF9D] animate-pulse\" />\n411 |             LOCAL_SANDBOX_CONNECTED\n412 |           </span>\n413 |         </div>\n414 |       </div>\n415 | \n416 |       <AnimatePresence mode=\"wait\">\n417 |         {!showResults && !isCompiling && (\n418 |           <motion.div\n419 |             key=\"wizard\"\n420 |             initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 15 }}\n421 |             animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}\n422 |             exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -15 }}\n423 |             transition={{ duration: 0.35, ease: \"easeOut\" }}\n424 |             className=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 items-start\"\n425 |           >\n426 |             {/* Left Column: Form Steps */}\n427 |             <form onSubmit={handleCompile} className=\"lg:col-span-8 space-y-6\">\n428 |               <div className=\"p-6 lg:p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/5 bg-[#030306]/90 min-h-[480px] flex flex-col justify-between relative overflow-hidden\">\n429 |                 <div className=\"absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-[1px] bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[#009DFF]/30 to-transparent pointer-events-none\" />\n430 | \n431 |                 <div className=\"space-y-6\">\n432 |                   {/* Step Indicators */}\n433 |                   <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center border-b border-white/5 pb-4\">\n434 |                     <div className=\"flex gap-1.5\">\n435 |                       {([1, 2, 3] as const).map((step) => (\n436 |                         <button\n437 |                           key={step}\n438 |                           type=\"button\"\n439 |                           onClick={() => {\n440 |                             if (step < currentStep || (step === 2 && data.desc.trim().length >= 15)) {\n441 |                               setCurrentStep(step);\n442 |                               setValidationError(null);\n443 |                             }\n444 |                           }}\n445 |                           className={`h-6 px-2.5 rounded text-[10px] font-mono font-bold uppercase transition flex items-center gap-1.5 border ${\n446 |                             currentStep === step\n447 |                               ? \"bg-[#009DFF]/10 text-[#009DFF] border-[#009DFF]/25\"\n448 |                               : step < currentStep\n449 |                               ? \"bg-white/5 text-white/60 border-white/5 hover:text-white\"\n450 |                               : \"bg-transparent text-white/20 border-transparent cursor-not-allowed\"\n451 |                           }`}\n452 |                           disabled={step > currentStep && (step === 3 || data.desc.trim().length < 15)}\n453 |                         >\n454 |                           <span>GATE 0{step}</span>\n455 |                           {step < currentStep && (\n456 |                             <svg className=\"w-2.5 h-2.5 text-[#00FF9D]\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n457 |                               <path strokeLinecap=\"round\" strokeLinejoin=\"round\" strokeWidth={3} d=\"M5 13l4 4L19 7\" />\n458 |                             </svg>\n459 |                           )}\n460 |                         </button>\n461 |                       ))}\n462 |                     </div>\n463 |                     <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/30 uppercase tracking-widest\">\n464 |                       STEP {currentStep} OF 3\n465 |                     </span>\n466 |                   </div>\n467 | \n468 |                   {/* Step 1: Bottleneck Details */}\n469 |                   {currentStep === 1 && (\n470 |                     <div className=\"space-y-4 animate-fadeIn\">\n471 |                       <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n472 |                         <h2\n473 |                           ref={stepHeaderRef}\n474 |                           tabIndex={-1}\n475 |                           className=\"text-lg font-bold text-white outline-none focus:ring-0\"\n476 |                         >\n477 |                           Identify the Core Operational Friction\n478 |                         </h2>\n479 |                         <p className=\"text-xs text-white/45 font-light leading-relaxed\">\n480 |                           Describe the manual bottlenecks, database search lags, or redundant process validation loops in your organization.\n481 |                         </p>\n482 |                       </div>\n483 | \n484 |                       {/* Clickable Examples */}\n485 |                       <div className=\"p-4 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-white/[0.01] space-y-3\">\n486 |                         <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-white/45 uppercase tracking-wider block\">\n487 |                           CHOOSE AN ENTERPRISE EXAMPLE TO PREFILL:\n488 |                         </span>\n489 |                         <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3\">\n490 |                           {examples.map((ex, idx) => (\n491 |                             <button\n492 |                               key={idx}\n493 |                               type=\"button\"\n494 |                               onClick={() => handlePrefillExample(ex.full)}\n495 |                               className=\"text-left p-3.5 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-[#030305] hover:border-[#009DFF]/40 hover:bg-white/[0.02] transition-all group relative focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF] focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[#009DFF]\"\n496 |                             >\n497 |                               <div\n498 |                                 className=\"absolute top-0 left-0 w-1 h-full rounded-l transition-all bg-[#009DFF] group-hover:bg-[#009DFF]/80\"\n499 |                               />\n500 |                               <h3 className=\"text-xs font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-[#009DFF] transition-colors ml-2\">\n501 |                                 {ex.title}\n502 |                               </h3>\n503 |                               <p className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40 font-light mt-1 line-clamp-1 ml-2\">\n504 |                                 {ex.short}\n505 |                               </p>\n506 |                             </button>\n507 |                           ))}\n508 |                         </div>\n509 |                       </div>\n510 | \n511 |                       <div className=\"space-y-2\">\n512 |                         <label htmlFor=\"challenge-desc\" className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wider block\">\n513 |                           Operational Friction Description <span className=\"text-[#E4000F] font-bold\">*</span>\n514 |                         </label>\n515 |                         <div className=\"relative\">\n516 |                           <textarea\n517 |                             id=\"challenge-desc\"\n518 |                             ref={textareaRef}\n519 |                             rows={5}\n520 |                             value={data.desc}\n521 |                             onChange={(e) => {\n522 |                               setData((prev) => ({ ...prev, desc: e.target.value }));\n523 |                               if (validationError) setValidationError(null);\n524 |                             }}\n525 |                             placeholder=\"Describe the operational bottleneck (e.g. Employees spend too much time searching for information...)\"\n526 |                             className=\"w-full rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-black text-white p-4 focus:border-[#009DFF] focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF]/30 outline-none text-xs resize-none leading-relaxed font-light transition-all\"\n527 |                             aria-required=\"true\"\n528 |                             maxLength={1000}\n529 |                           />\n530 |                           <div className=\"absolute bottom-3 right-3 text-[9px] font-mono text-white/30\">\n531 |                             {data.desc.length} / 1000 CHARS\n532 |                           </div>\n533 |                         </div>\n534 |                       </div>\n535 |                     </div>\n536 |                   )}\n537 | \n538 |                   {/* Step 2: Industry & Organization Size */}\n539 |                   {currentStep === 2 && (\n540 |                     <div className=\"space-y-6 animate-fadeIn\">\n541 |                       <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n542 |                         <h2 ref={stepHeaderRef} tabIndex={-1} className=\"text-lg font-bold text-white outline-none\">\n543 |                           Organization & Domain Scope\n544 |                         </h2>\n545 |                         <p className=\"text-xs text-white/45 font-light leading-relaxed\">\n546 |                           Define your operational domain and company bracket to shape the regulatory compliance constraints.\n547 |                         </p>\n548 |                       </div>\n549 | \n550 |                       {/* Industry grid selector */}\n551 |                       <div className=\"space-y-3\">\n552 |                         <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wider block\">\n553 |                           Select Industry Domain\n554 |                         </span>\n555 |                         <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-3\">\n556 |                           {indOptions.map((opt) => {\n557 |                             const isSelected = data.ind === opt.id;\n558 |                             return (\n559 |                               <button\n560 |                                 key={opt.id}\n561 |                                 type=\"button\"\n562 |                                 onClick={() => setData((prev) => ({ ...prev, ind: opt.id }))}\n563 |                                 className={`text-left p-4 rounded-xl border transition-all relative group flex gap-3 focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF] focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[#009DFF] ${\n564 |                                   isSelected\n565 |                                     ? \"bg-white/[0.03] border-white/10\"\n566 |                                     : \"bg-white/[0.01] border-white/5 hover:border-white/10 hover:bg-white/[0.02]\"\n567 |                                 }`}\n568 |                                 aria-pressed={isSelected}\n569 |                               >\n570 |                                 {isSelected && (\n571 |                                   <div\n572 |                                     className=\"absolute inset-x-0 top-0 h-[1.5px]\"\n573 |                                     style={{\n574 |                                       background: `linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, ${opt.accentColor}, transparent)`,\n575 |                                     }}\n576 |                                   />\n577 |                                 )}\n578 |                                 <div\n579 |                                   className={`w-7 h-7 rounded-lg border flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 transition-colors ${\n580 |                                     isSelected\n581 |                                       ? \"bg-white/5 border-white/10\"\n582 |                                       : \"bg-white/[0.01] border-white/5 text-white/30\"\n583 |                                   }`}\n584 |                                   style={isSelected ? { color: opt.accentColor, borderColor: `${opt.accentColor}25` } : {}}\n585 |                                 >\n586 |                                   {opt.icon}\n587 |                                 </div>\n588 |                                 <div className=\"space-y-0.5\">\n589 |                                   <span className=\"text-xs font-bold text-white block\">\n590 |                                     {opt.title}\n591 |                                   </span>\n592 |                                   <p className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40 leading-snug font-light\">\n593 |                                     {opt.description}\n594 |                                   </p>\n595 |                                 </div>\n596 |                               </button>\n597 |                             );\n598 |                           })}\n599 |                         </div>\n600 |                       </div>\n601 | \n602 |                       {/* Company size selector */}\n603 |                       <div className=\"space-y-3 pt-2\">\n604 |                         <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wider block\">\n605 |                           Company Size Bracket\n606 |                         </span>\n607 |                         <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3\">\n608 |                           {sizeOptions.map((opt) => {\n609 |                             const isSelected = data.size === opt.id;\n610 |                             return (\n611 |                               <button\n612 |                                 key={opt.id}\n613 |                                 type=\"button\"\n614 |                                 onClick={() => setData((prev) => ({ ...prev, size: opt.id }))}\n615 |                                 className={`text-left p-3.5 rounded-xl border transition-all focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF] focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[#009DFF] ${\n616 |                                   isSelected\n617 |                                     ? \"bg-white/[0.03] border-white/15\"\n618 |                                     : \"bg-white/[0.01] border-white/5 hover:border-white/10 hover:bg-white/[0.02]\"\n619 |                                 }`}\n620 |                                 aria-pressed={isSelected}\n621 |                               >\n622 |                                 <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center\">\n623 |                                   <span className=\"text-xs font-bold text-white\">{opt.title}</span>\n624 |                                   {isSelected && (\n625 |                                     <span className=\"w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#009DFF]\" />\n626 |                                   )}\n627 |                                 </div>\n628 |                                 <p className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40 font-light mt-1 leading-snug\">\n629 |                                   {opt.description}\n630 |                                 </p>\n631 |                               </button>\n632 |                             );\n633 |                           })}\n634 |                         </div>\n635 |                       </div>\n636 |                     </div>\n637 |                   )}\n638 | \n639 |                   {/* Step 3: Optional Strategic Parameters */}\n640 |                   {currentStep === 3 && (\n641 |                     <div className=\"space-y-6 animate-fadeIn\">\n642 |                       <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n643 |                         <h2 ref={stepHeaderRef} tabIndex={-1} className=\"text-lg font-bold text-white outline-none\">\n644 |                           Tactical Deployment Settings\n645 |                         </h2>\n646 |                         <p className=\"text-xs text-white/45 font-light leading-relaxed\">\n647 |                           Define optional scheduling, regional boundaries, and operational stages to complete the strategy compilation.\n648 |                         </p>\n649 |                       </div>\n650 | \n651 |                       <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5\">\n652 |                         {/* Geography Selection */}\n653 |                         <div className=\"space-y-2\">\n654 |                           <label htmlFor=\"geo-select\" className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-wider block\">\n655 |                             Target Geography (Optional)\n656 |                           </label>\n657 |                           <select\n658 |                             id=\"geo-select\"\n659 |                             value={data.geography}\n660 |                             onChange={(e) => setData((prev) => ({ ...prev, geography: e.target.value }))}\n661 |                             className=\"w-full h-10 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-black text-white px-3 text-xs outline-none focus:border-[#009DFF] transition-all\"\n662 |                           >\n663 |                             <option value=\"\">No explicit geographical boundary</option>\n664 |                             {geoOptions.map((opt) => (\n665 |                               <option key={opt.id} value={opt.id}>{opt.label}</option>\n666 |                             ))}\n667 |                           </select>\n668 |                         </div>\n669 | \n670 |                         {/* Deployment Urgency */}\n671 |                         <div clas