nd the ${data.engagementPathObj.label} path (${data.engagementPathObj.badge}) deployed completely isolated on single-tenant architecture within ${data.geographyLabel} with a strict zero data-retention layer.\n281 | \n282 | SECTION IV: PROPOSED WORKSTREAMS\n283 | - Workstream A: Hardened Perimeter Setup (Weeks 1 - ${p1}): Configure VPC boundaries and verify zero-retention.\n284 | - Workstream B: Pipeline Core Integration (Weeks ${p1 + 1} - ${p1 + p2}): Deploy OmniMesh read-only connectors and metadata layers.\n285 | - Workstream C: Agent Orchestration & Tuning (Weeks ${p1 + p2 + 1} - ${p1 + p2 + p3}): Standardize agent configurations and workflow guardrails.\n286 | - Workstream D: Telemetry Logging & Handoff (Weeks ${p1 + p2 + p3 + 1} - ${weeks}): Integrate real-time audit ledgers and operator dashboards.\n287 | \n288 | SECTION V: 90-DAY ROADMAP\n289 | - Day 1-30: Perimeter Isolation: Connect legacy data silos via OmniMesh read-only boundaries.\n290 | - Day 31-60: Agent Workflow Design: Orchestrate multi-agent decision nodes and feedback loops.\n291 | - Day 61-90: Go-Live & Certification: Scale the agent fleet and complete sovereign compliance certification.\n292 | \n293 | SECTION VI: SUGGESTED SQUAD\n294 | Squad cohort: ${data.engagementPathObj.squad}\n295 | - Lead Solutions Architect (VPC & data boundary configuration)\n296 | - Systems Engineers (local weight tuning & pipeline performance)\n297 | - Security Compliance Auditor (zero-retention validation logging)\n298 | \n299 | SECTION VII: GOVERNANCE APPROACH\n300 | GFF enforces a \"Zero Trust, Zero Retention\" sovereign AI governance framework. Prompt-history is instantly zeroed out post-execution, and telemetry logs are recorded to a read-only audit ledger.\n301 | \n302 | SECTION VIII: SUCCESS MEASURES\n303 | - Latency: Sub-150ms dynamic cognitive decision loops.\n304 | - IP Safety: Absolute zero external IP leaks or SaaS memory retention logs.\n305 | - OpEx Reclamation: 30%+ reclaimed external SaaS token and lice