{"ts":"2026-06-26T23:33:39.093Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"zvjg1h8v","input":{"summary":"### Phase 3 UX Polish: Build with GFF Tools Refinement\n\nWe have systematically refined and polished the empty states, loading-like transitions, error states, validation states, completion states, and reset states across all 8 Build with GFF tools: `/build/talk`, `/build/blueprint`, `/build/assessment`, `/build/roi`, `/build/sandbox`, `/build/proposal`, `/build/marketplace`, and `/build/foundry-studio`.\n\n#### Key Improvements Implemented:\n1. **Premium Isolated Purge States (Reset Visuals)**:\n   - Implemented a standard, high-fidelity visual cache-purging transition (`isFlushing` / `isFlushingLogs`) of 450ms across tools when clearing state or resetting inputs. This displays a beautiful secure terminal wiping progress bar stating `\"Scrubbing Workspace Buffer: PURGING_SECURE_CLIENT_CACHE\"`.\n   \n2. **Removed AI Slop Native Browser Alerts**:\n   - Replaced raw browser `alert()` calls in `/build/marketplace`, `/build/foundry-studio`, and `/build/proposal` (such as maximum comparison limits, signatory checks, and topology constraints) with custom, elegant, in-page and floating toast notifications styled in the GFF AI dark-mode design theme.\n   - For `/build/foundry-studio`, validation errors are logged directly to the active pseudo-terminal as `[TOPOLOGY RULE CONSTRAINT] ...` warnings, enhancing the immersive feel of senior strategic software.\n\n3. **Polished Loader & Transition Animations**:\n   - Refined deterministic loaders using custom, lightweight Tailwind/CSS scanning lines, spin animations, and state traces inside the secure enclaves.\n\n4. **Robust Layouts & Safe Tree Parsing**:\n   - Resolved TSX bracket-matching issues in `/build/roi` by implementing a clean, React Fragment (`<>`) wrapping pattern for the ternary branches, ensuring 100% build compatibility and zero visual shift.\n\nThe entire build (`npm run build`) compiles successfully without any errors or warnings, and is ready for production.","verified":true}}}
